bilingual.source: I walked through the corner and into the shop.
The children went through the gate into the castle.
bilingual.target: 孩子们穿过大门进入城堡。

bilingual.source: Later in the day, people came into the forest.
bilingual.target: 当天晚些时候，人们进入了森林。

bilingual.source: Tanks came into Alex's school grounds, too!
bilingual.target: 坦克也进入了亚历克斯的学校操场！

bilingual.source: You cannot go into someone's house with your shoes on.
bilingual.target: 你不能穿着鞋进入别人的房子。

bilingual.source: Yuri Gagarin became the first person in the world to go into space.
bilingual.target: 尤里·加加林成为世界上第一个进入太空的人。

bilingual.source: Sending astronauts into space has helped people to think about the world's problems.
bilingual.target: 送宇航员进入太空帮助人们思考世界问题。

bilingual.source: Although she faced many obstacles, Rankin made it possible for more women to go into politics.
bilingual.target: 尽管她面临许多障碍，兰金使更多女性进入政界成为可能。

bilingual.source: On 12 April 1961, Yuri Gagarin became the first person in the world to go into space.
bilingual.target: 1961年4月12日，尤里·加加林成为世界上第一个进入太空的人。
骑士向前骑马进入战斗。

list.abstract: into（英[ˈɪntu]，美[ˈɪntu]），英语单词，介词，释义为进；入；到…里面。短语搭配为turn into（变成）。例句为“You have to fight your way into the carriage, and keep away from others' hot water.（你必须拼命挤进车厢，远离别人的热水。）”
INTO是由深圳引途信息科技有限公司开发的软件，致力为访华/在华外国友人解决各种生活难题，定位为“外国人的中国通”。App的标语是“INTO， 意思是像本地人一样生活和旅游”。

yingyinNormal.en: Anything to put a Democrat into the governor's mansion.
yingyinNormal.zh: 能让民主党人进入州长府邸就好。

yingyinNormal.en: Don't go into the radiation zone. Don't ask too many questions.
yingyinNormal.zh: 别进入辐射区。别问太多问题。

yingyinNormal.en: And there's no other way into the computer lab? No other way in.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没有其他途径进入电脑室了吗？没有。

yingyinNormal.en: Not locking into a path too early gave me an opportunity to go into a new and life changing field.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没有太早锁死自己的道路，让我有机会进入改变生活的全新领域。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《Facebook COO谢丽尔·桑德伯格哈佛演讲》

yingyinNormal.en: I earned my Master's in Criminal Justice and got into the academy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我拿到了犯罪学的硕士学位，顺利进入警校。

yingyinNormal.en: Our drones spotted her crossing the border into the United States.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们的无人机侦察到她越过国界进入了美国境内

yingyinNormal.en: Odessa, what is it you call it when he goes into one of his little places?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那叫什么，当他又进入自己的世界的时候？

yingyinNormal.en: It's like I've stepped through a time warp into some sci-fi future.
yingyinNormal.zh: 就像进入了一个时间隧道，到达了科幻的世界。

yingyinNormal.en: Look at them. They're going into the human world, and they don't even look scared!
yingyinNormal.zh: 瞧他们，他们要进入人类世界却一点都不吓人。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, it is the gosh-darnedest thing. Hard-scrabble's letting us into the Scare program.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真是碰到鬼了呢。郝刻薄让我们进入惊吓课程。

yingyinNormal.en: There you go. Now any e-mail from Wolowitz will go right into your spam folder.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了，现在所有沃尔伍兹发来的邮件都会直接进入垃圾箱。

yingyinNormal.en: You used the tunnels to infiltrate yourself into the White House, somehow conning your way into the blue sector, all to try and warn her?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你之前从隧道侵入白宫，还想办法进入到了蓝区，你做这些都是为了警告她吗

yingyinNormal.en: Now, this is important. Once the battery is removed, everything is gonna slam into emergency mode.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这一点很重要，电池一被移走，监狱进入紧急模式。

yingyinNormal.en: They could get uplifted into a mountain range and eroded away or carried along in an oceanic plate and subducted back into the Earth's mantle, melting your fossil into hot mush.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们可能因为地壳上升成为山脉又被侵蚀流失或是随着大洋板块潜没又进入地幔，将你的化石熔化。

yingyinNormal.en: If we're gonna get out of here, we're gonna need to get into that watchtower. And to do that, I'm gonna need a few things.
yingyinNormal.zh: 想逃走就得进入那座了望台，所以需要几样东西。

yingyinNormal.en: That's why you guys put us into a safe place. That's not the safe place. That's a hole.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以你们让我们进入安全地带。那不是什么安全地带，那只是个洞。

yingyinNormal.en: But the future, our future starts tomorrow at dawn. When we march together into the Capitol.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但未来我们的未来，将在明日黎明我们进入国会区之时峥嵘初现。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, it's very faint, but I can still sense him in the building. Go into the light, Mr. Heckles!
yingyinNormal.zh: 很微弱，但我还可以感觉他在大楼里，进入光芒中，哈克先生！

yingyinNormal.en: Exactly. If we didn't do it, these students would never get into another institution.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没错，如果我们没有这样做的话，这些学生可能永远都不会有进入高校的机会。

yingyinNormal.en: We're already hearing this is gonna be a very long lockout. We're about to go into the nuclear winter of the NBA.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们已经听说这将是一个长期的停摆，我们将进入NBA的严冬。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2015-2022年全国卷高考试卷，包括阅读、完形、单选、填空、听力、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选各省市考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Jeff broke two eggs <highlight>into</highlight> a plate and added in some milk.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 杰夫往盘子里打了两个鸡蛋，又加了一些牛奶。

examination_example.sentence: You can't help wondering how hard it was for the people then to put all those rocks <highlight>into</highlight> place.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你不禁会想，当时人们把这些石头放回原处有多难。

examination_example.sentence: Since 1934, better than half a billion dollars has gone <highlight>into</highlight> that Fund to purchase more than 5 million acres of habitat.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 自1934年以来，超过5亿美元已投入该基金，用于购买500多万英亩的栖息地。

examination_example.sentence: It burst <highlight>into</highlight> hundreds of pieces.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它炸成了数百块碎片。

examination_example.sentence: Running the website has almost turned <highlight>into</highlight> a full-time job.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 运营网站几乎变成了一份全职工作。

examination_example.sentence: Jenna threw the burnt piece <highlight>into</highlight> the sink and put in the other slice of bread.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 詹娜把烤焦的那块扔进水槽，放入另一片面包。

examination_example.sentence: Let's look directly <highlight>into</highlight> the issue of collapse.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 让我们直接看看崩溃的问题。

examination_example.sentence: To look <highlight>into</highlight> the case, Wang disguised (伪装) himself and joined the beggars.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为了调查这件事，王乔装打扮，加入了乞丐的行列。

examination_example.sentence: I began looking <highlight>into</highlight> college courses for Fashion Design and three months later I signed up for a part-time design course.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我开始研究大学的时装设计课程，三个月后，我报名参加了一个兼职设计课程。

examination_example.sentence: Everyone in the family settled quickly <highlight>into</highlight> the city except me.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 除了我，家里的每个人都很快适应了这个城市。

examination_example.sentence: Finally you climb <highlight>into</highlight> an arctic-like zone with permanent snow and the glaciers that may soon disappear.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最后，你会爬进一个像北极一样的地带，那里常年积雪，冰川可能很快就会消失。

examination_example.sentence: The Newcastle team are developing in-vehicle technologies for older drivers which they hope could help them to continue driving <highlight>into</highlight> later life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 纽卡斯尔团队正在为老年司机开发车载技术，他们希望这可以帮助他们在晚年继续驾驶。

examination_example.sentence: Cafes focused around psychology, history, and engineering are catching on, filling tables well <highlight>into</highlight> the evening.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 专注于心理学、历史学和工程学的咖啡馆正在流行起来，桌子上一直到晚上都挤满了顾客。

examination_example.sentence: These expansions <highlight>into</highlight> new worlds help us by giving us new perspectives.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些对新世界的扩展通过给我们新的视角来帮助我们。

examination_example.sentence: My kids and I were heading <highlight>into</highlight> the supermarket over the weekend.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我和我的孩子周末去超市。

examination_example.sentence: I pays to put theory <highlight>into</highlight> practice.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我努力把理论付诸实践。

examination_example.sentence: She's been able to put a lot of what she's learnt <highlight>into</highlight> practice in her own home.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她已经能够在自己家里将所学的许多东西付诸实践。

examination_example.sentence: Through the years, I'd run <highlight>into</highlight> former students who would provide updates on old classmates.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些年来，我遇到了以前的学生，他们会提供老同学的最新消息。

examination_example.sentence: Taken <highlight>into</highlight> account.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 考虑在内。

examination_example.sentence: I let a salesclerk fool me <highlight>into</highlight> buying a discontinued model.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一个售货员骗我买了一个停产的型号。

examination_example.sentence: I think my home falls <highlight>into</highlight> that category.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我想我的家属于那一类。

examination_example.sentence: I took off my T-shirt and dived <highlight>into</highlight> the water.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我脱下t恤，跳入水中。

examination_example.sentence: I was, nevertheless, talked <highlight>into</highlight> going on another fun-filled holiday in the wilderness.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 尽管如此，我还是被说服去进行另一次充满乐趣的荒野之旅。

examination_example.sentence: Young people are being forced <highlight>into</highlight> earning money before finishing their education.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 年轻人被迫在完成学业前赚钱。

examination_example.sentence: They love feeding the fruit and frozen bananas <highlight>into</highlight> the top of the machine and watching the ice cream come out below.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们喜欢把水果和冷冻香蕉放进机器顶部，看着冰淇淋从下面出来。

examination_example.sentence: When I handed him the gift card, saying he could use it for whatever his family might need, he burst <highlight>into</highlight> tears.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当我把礼品卡递给他，说他可以用它来支付家人可能需要的任何费用时，他突然哭了起来。

examination_example.sentence: What happened to the ice around the ship when the ship moved <highlight>into</highlight> the ice？
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当船进入冰时，船周围的冰发生了什么变化？

examination_example.sentence: They went <highlight>into</highlight> a shop.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们走进一家商店。

examination_example.sentence: The young fish swim down the river to the sea and <highlight>into</highlight> the Atlantic Ocean.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 小鱼顺流而下，游向大海，进入大西洋。

examination_example.sentence: Steel and aluminum cans can be melted down and made <highlight>into</highlight> new cans.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 钢罐和铝罐可以被熔化并制成新罐。

examination_example.sentence: The first one is never to turn the conversation <highlight>into</highlight> an argument.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 第一点是绝不要把谈话变成争论。

examination_example.sentence: So take your time and I believe you will grow <highlight>into</highlight> an excellent young man.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 所以慢慢来，我相信你会成长为一个优秀的年轻人。
